## Flags — `web/src/assets/flags/`
Downloaded from **Wikimedia Commons** (`commons.wikimedia.org`) by
`web/scripts/download-flags.mjs`, one SVG per team. Most national flags are in the
public domain, but licensing varies per file — check each file's page on Wikimedia
Commons.

## Broadcaster logos — `web/src/assets/broadcasters/`
Downloaded from **Wikimedia Commons** by `web/scripts/download-broadcasters.mjs`
(ARD, ZDF, RTL, Sky, DAZN, Eurosport, MagentaTV, Prime Video, Netflix, …). These are
**trademarks and logos of their respective broadcasters**, used nominatively to show
where a match airs. All trademark rights remain with the owners.

## Federation crests — `web/src/assets/team-logos/`
Extracted from the infoboxes of the relevant **English / German Wikipedia** articles
by `web/scripts/download-team-logos.mjs`, or uploaded by an admin (e.g. from
football-logos.cc) via the Mannschaften tab. National-association crests (the DFB
eagle, the Three Lions, …) are **copyrighted trademarks of their federations**,
typically hosted on Wikipedia under fair-use terms. They are not relicensed here.

## Match data — api-football
Live and historical match data comes from **api-football** (api-sports.io) under its
own terms of service and requires your own API key. No api-football data is
redistributed in this repository.
